Usage: trimDesign [-help] [-coreToBoundary <micron>]
                  [-dir <output_dir_to_save_trimmed_design>]
                  [-encryptName <proc_name_to_encrypt>]
                  [-name <trim_design_name>] [-nets <list_of_net_names>]
                  [-placeOnly] [-area <box_co_ordinates> | -polygon <list_of_points> | -selectedRouteBlk ]

-help                                   # Prints out the command usage
-area <box_co_ordinates>                # List of points for box end
                                        # coordinates. (string, required)
-coreToBoundary <micron>                # any instance lying within the
                                        # distance of coreToBoundary (in
                                        # microns) to the trim box will be
                                        # discarded. Default: is 2 times the
                                        # pitch of second routing layer
                                        # (string, optional)
-dir <output_dir_to_save_trimmed_design>
                                        # Directory in which data related to
                                        # trimmed-design will get saved
                                        # (string, optional)
-encryptName <proc_name_to_encrypt>     # To encrypt names of instances and
                                        # nets in design while saving trimmmed
                                        # design (string, optional)
-name <trim_design_name>                # Top-level name of new trimmed-design
                                        # (string, optional)
-nets <list_of_net_names>               # To specify nets to be completely
                                        # enclosed by the specified shape by
                                        # taking union of shape with net-boxes
                                        # (string, optional)
-placeOnly                              # Flag for pushing instances only
                                        # (bool, optional)
-polygon <list_of_points>               # List of points to represent polygon.
                                        # (string, required)
-selectedRouteBlk                       # Selected routing blockages, which
                                        # will be used to infer box or polygon
                                        # (bool, required)